\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Unified treatment of the asymptotics of asymmetric kernel density estimators
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Till Hoffmann
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Nick Jones
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
We show that there are two fundamentally different approaches to constructing
 density estimators from asymmetric kernels: the first approach is widely
 used but does not yield normalised densities.
 The second approach has been neglected until recently.
 We argue that kernels of the first kind can be approximated by symmetric
 kernels whose bandwidth depends on where they are evaluated.
 Kernels of the second kind converge to symmetric kernels whose bandwidth
 depends on the associated sample.
 We derive the asymptotic bias, variance and mean (integrated) square error
 of the two approximations and apply our approach to gamma, log-normal,
 Birnbaum-Saunders, inverse Gaussian, and reciprocal inverse Gaussian kernels.
 We confirm expressions for the asymptotic properties of asymmetric kernel
 density estimators found in the literature, introduce two new estimators
 of the second kind, derive plugin bandwidth estimators, and provide a unified
 approach to evaluate the asymptotic properties of density estimators with
 asymmetric kernels.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
