\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "tbl:kernels"

\end_inset

List of probability distributions with their mean and variance.
 The fourth column shows the parametrisation used for irregular estimators,
 where 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is the evaluation point and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 is the associated sample.
 The parametrisation for regular estimators can be obtained by swapping
 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

.
 The fifth column lists the shift between the mean of the kernel and the
 sample.
 The effective bandwidth is shown in the last column.
 The last row shows an alternative parametrisation for the RIG kernel.
 See the main text for details.
\end_layout

\end_inset


